author: Savannah Morning News
title: Savannah State University's fine arts building closed after early morning fire
text:
By Savannah Morning News Savannah State University's John F. Kennedy Fine Arts Building is closed after fire broke out early Wednesday morning, according to The Tiger's Roar.
Students with classes in the building are advised to contact their professors.
